title: Too, Too Solid Flesh by Nick O'Donohoe (EPUB MOBI AZW3 PDF)
description:
In the bleak, terrifying techno-world of a not-so-distant future, great cultural works are recycled as biochip implants and simulated ghost images. Hamlet is the star, director, and brooding conscience of an android repertory troupe created for the priviliged thrill-seekers of decadent Manhattan society.

Only now, the human creator of the android ensemble has been brutally murdered, and Hamlet must stalk the fiend. He descends into the depths of the Orwellian society he has been programmed to serve, in order learn a terrible about the killer - and about himself.
